BUILD KERNEL
============

#NOTE --> before execute  commands bottom need mount "/boot" and "/boot/efi" partitions   
#---
1. cryptsetup open /dev/sda2 encrypted_boot
2. mount /dev/mapper/encrypted_boot /boot/
3. mount /dev/sda1  /boot/efi/
#---

##kernel amd initramfs create
make -j9 && make -j9 modules_install && make install

genkernel --lvm --luks initramfs

#update grub
grub-mkconfig -o /boot/grub/grub.cfg

#when you will be get stable kernel you need make stable copy, for recovery boot
#example -->

-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 4512223 Aug  2 23:14 System.map-4.12.12-gentoo-stable
-rw-r--r-- 1 root root  113967 Aug  2 23:14 config-4.12.12-gentoo-stable
-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 2870716 Aug  2 23:14 initramfs-genkernel-x86_64-4.12.12-gentoo-stable
-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 9990096 Aug  2 23:14 vmlinuz-4.12.12-gentoo-stable

and fix grub.conf with your hands
